Program: Omnibus
Title: All Four Engines
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0376l7t
Last Broadcast Date: 26 June 1996
'Flying into the pages of aviation history'. Recounting the story of BA flight 9 in 1982 when all four engines failed on a Boeing 747 after flying through a cloud of volcanic dust. Includes interviews with surviving passengers and flight crew members Eric Moody, Roger Greaves, Graham Skinner and Barry Townley-Freeman. Show less